MOTORISTS faced disruption after a three-car crash on the M74.The collision happened during rush hour on Wednesday, shortly after 6pm.Polmadie Road was closed to traffic between the M74 Northbound on/off ramps and Calder Street.Road users were advised to avoid the area.It was not clear how many people were injured, however a spokeswoman from the Scottish Ambulance Service said one ambulance transported people to the Victoria Infirmary.Their injuries did not appear to be life threatening.The road was reopened at about 7.30pm.